This method should account for combined rect of children, at the moment it doesn't

inside UIElement::GetCombinedScreenRect()
the portion:

            IntVector2 childPos = (*i)->GetScreenPosition();
            const IntVector2& childSize = (*i)->GetSize();

should be like this if I'm not mistaken

            IntRect childCombined((*i)->GetCombinedScreenRect());
            IntVector2 childPos(childCombined.left_,childCombined.top_);
            const IntVector2& childSize(childCombined.right_-childCombined.left_,childCombined.bottom_-childCombined.top_);

Since HiresTick() supposed to return the time in microseconds
timeGetTime() returns the time in milliseconds , hence it should be multiplied by 1000.

Should be :
    if (HiresTimer::IsSupported())
    {
        LARGE_INTEGER counter;
        QueryPerformanceCounter(&counter);
        return counter.QuadPart;
    }
    else
        **return timeGetTime() \* 1000; // should be converted into microseconds**

